<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_with_attributes  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes">
A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> is a type of <b>Class</b> that may be defined with a set of valued parameters.
<example>A standard type of screws can be classified according to its head type, its diameter and its length.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_with_attributes  Attribute: version_id 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.version_id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.version_id">
the identification of a particular version of a <b>Class_with_attributes</b>. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_with_attributes  Attribute: used_classification_system 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.used_classification_system"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.used_classification_system">
the <b>Classification_system</b> that contains the information about the definition of the classification and how to interpret the name of the <b>Class_with_attributes</b>. 
The value of the attribute need not be specified.

<example>
<p>For facilitating an effective part retrieval for slotted screws, several instances of <b>Class_with_attributes</b> may be defined to classify screws: 
</p><ul>
<li>A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *1 with description 'slotted screws' and the following three subclasses 
</li><li>A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *2 with description 'slotted cheese head screws - product grade A', 
</li><li>A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *3 with description 'slotted pan head screws - product grade A', and 
</li><li>A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *4 with description 'slotted countersunk flat head screws - product grade A'.
</li></ul>
<p> 
Each of these instances is based on a Classification_system that further defines where the definition of the classification comes from. 
For *1, this is a company internal Classification_system for 'screw classes'. 
For the other instances, these are Classification_system instances identifying ISO standards, 
namely for *2 'ISO 1207', for *3 'ISO 1580', and for *4 'ISO 2009'. 
</p>
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_with_attributes  Attribute: characterization_attributes 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.characterization_attributes"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.characterization_attributes">
the <b>Classification_attribute</b> instances that characterize the <b>Class_with_attributes</b>.
<example>
According to ISO 1207, the <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *2 has the attributes *11 with id 'd' and name 'thread', 
*12 with id 'l' and name 'nominal length', *13 with id 'mechanical properties' and name 'property class', and so on. 
The possible values 'M1.6', 'M2', ..., 'M10' for Classification_attribute *11 may be defined as instances of a subtype of Measure_item. 
The thread class name, 'M1.6', 'M2', ..., is represented within the name attribute of the referenced instances of Measure_item. 
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: External_class_with_attributes  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.External_class_with_attributes"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.External_class_with_attributes">
An <b>External_class_with_attributes</b> is a type of <b>Class_with_attributes</b> that is defined in an external library.
<example>
The classification may be defined in an ISO 13584 compliant library (PLIB). 
In this case, the <b>External_class_with_attributes</b> references as a classification source a <b>Plib_class_reference</b> that has an id corresponding to the class_BSU, 
that is a world wide unique identification of that class as defined according to ISO 13584-42.
</example>

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: External_class_with_attributes  Attribute: source 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.External_class_with_attributes.source"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.External_class_with_attributes.source">
the <b>Plib_class_reference</b> or <b>External_class</b> that identifies the external specification of the <b>External_class_with_attributes</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association">
A <b>Classification_association</b> is a type of <b>Classification_assignment</b> that associates a <b>Class_with_attributes</b> with product or activity data.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  Attribute: assigned_grouping 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.assigned_grouping"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.assigned_grouping">
the <b>Class_with_attributes</b> instance that provides classification information.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  Attribute: definitional 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.definitional"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.definitional">
a logical value that specifies whether a <b>Class_with_attributes</b> serves as definition of the classified element.
A value of 'true' indicates that the <b>Class_with_attributes</b> is definitional.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.wr:WR1">
When definitional is true, the <b>Class_with_attributes</b> shall be assigned to instances of type <b>definable_objects</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.wr:WR2">
Only items of types listed in <b>classified_element_select</b> shall be referred to by a <b>Classification_association</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute">
A <b>Classification_attribute</b> is a characteristic of a <b>Class_with_attributes</b>.
A set of values may precise the allowed values of that characteristic.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: id 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.id">
the identifier of the <b>Classification_attribute</b>.
This identifier shall be unique within the scope of the associated <b>Class_with_attributes</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.name">
the word or group of words by which the <b>Classification_attribute</b> is referred to. 
The value of the attribute need not be specified.
<example>'length', 'width', or 'radius' are examples for the name of a Classification_attribute.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.description">
a text that provides additional information about the <b>Classification_attribute</b>. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: allowed_values 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.allowed_values"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.allowed_values">
the set of instances of <b>Measure_item</b> that specify the allowed values of the <b>Classification_attribute</b>. 
The value of the attribute need not be specified.
<note>The values may be specified as single values or value ranges.</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: characterized_class 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.characterized_class"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.characterized_class">
the <b>Class_with_attributes</b> of which the <b>Classification_attribute</b> defines a characteristic.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_system  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system">
A <b>Classification_system</b> identifies a scheme defining classifications of product or activity data.
<example>
A dictionary collecting the conventional definitions of technical properties is an example of Classification_system.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_system  Attribute: id 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system.id">
the identifier of the <b>Classification_system</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_system  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system.description">
a thext that provides additional information about the <b>Classification_system</b>. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
